                <p style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><br/></p>
                <div class="o_editor_banner o_not_editable lh-1 d-flex align-items-center alert alert-info pb-0 pt-3" data-oe-protected="true">
                    <i class="fs-4 fa fa-info-circle mb-3"></i>
                    <div class="o_editable o_editable_no_shadow w-100 ms-3" data-oe-protected="false">
                        <p>This setup is for sports clubs that rent courts to their players, handle some basic gears and have a cafeteria.</p>
                        <p style="margin-bottom: 0px;">As a small company,&nbsp;<strong>The Club</strong>&nbsp;still has quite a lot of activities to manage and does all this with Odoo.&nbsp;</p>
                        <p style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><br/></p>
                        <p style="margin-bottom: 0px;">Below are the detailed flows they use on a daily basis.</p>
                        <p style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><br/></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><br/></p>
                <h1>
                    <u><u>Flows</u></u>
                </h1>
                <p><br /></p>
                <h2>1. Gears<br /></h2>
                <hr/>
                <p>The Club Sells sport gears through 2 channels:</p>
                <p>
                    <br/>
                    a) Equipment can be bought on the Club eShop, with a <font class="text-o-color-1"><strong>paid delivery</strong></font> at home or a <strong><font class="text-o-color-1">free pick up</font></strong> at the Club, or directly from the
                    Club, through their dedicated "Shop" Point of Sale. When rackets are bought on the eShop, a basic <font class="text-o-color-1"><strong>up-sell</strong></font> is suggested: Add a towel or some balls to your order.
                </p>
                <p>
                    b) For players that need something on the spot, the <font class="text-o-color-1"><strong>SHOP </strong></font><font class="text-black">POS</font> <font class="text-black">can </font>also be used.&nbsp;
                </p>
                <p><br /></p>
                <h2>2. Bar Management<br/></h2>
                <hr />
                <p>
                    a) The&nbsp;Club has a bar where players can grab something to eat between games or have a beer.<br/>
                    It can be accessed in
                    <strong>
                        <font class="text-o-color-1">Point of Sales &gt; Bar </font><font class="text-black"><span style="font-weight: normal;">and contains some basic products.</span></font>
                    </strong>
                    <br/>
                    Customers can pay by through different means, including by adding the note to their account.
                </p>
                <p>
                    b) Planning for the Bar is also handled from Odoo. Simple <strong><font class="text-o-color-1">recurring shifts</font></strong> are created and assigned to the staff members.
                </p>
                <p><br/></p>
                <h2>3. Court Booking&nbsp;</h2>
                <hr />
                <p>
                    There are two appointment types configured for the Club.<br />
                    <br/>
                    a) The first one "<strong><font class="text-o-color-1">Court Booking</font></strong>" allows players to book a court for a session of 60 minutes.&nbsp;Slots start every 30 minutes.&nbsp;
                </p>
                <p>
                    b)&nbsp;The other one, "<strong><font class="text-o-color-1">Friday night free play"</font></strong>&nbsp;is only available on Fridays and allows player to&nbsp;join other games.
                </p>
                <blockquote data-o-mail-quote-node="1" data-o-mail-quote="1">Notes: This is because the courts are configured as shareable. As long as a free spot is left, players can register and share the resource (=the courts) with others.</blockquote>
                <p>
                    On top of that, employees working behind the counter can also take phone calls and book some courts. For this, they use the <strong><font class="text-o-color-1">Appointments &gt; Resource Schedule</font></strong> menu.&nbsp;
                </p>
                <p><br/></p>
